First Lady Melania Trump celebrated National Read Across America Day and Dr. Seuss's birthday by visiting a children's health center. She met with doctors, families, and patients, and shared the joy of reading with the children by reading Dr. Seuss books to them. Melania emphasized the importance of reading early in life and how it can make someone a lifelong learner. She praised Dr. Seuss for bringing joy and inspiration to children's lives while teaching them to read, dream, and care. Melania also stressed the significance of instilling a love of learning in young readers, as education is crucial for empowerment.